frameDefinitions: This is an abstract frame for acts performed by sentient beings.
An Agent expends effort towards achieving a Goal.
An Agent acts in a certain Manner either generally or under some particular Circumstances.
A Cognizer has carried out an approximate calculation or considered some Evidence and produced an approximation of the Value of a feature of an Item.
An Entity ends up with some Final_quality--a new fact about the Entity.
An Agent enacts an Action that is intended to be performed again at one or more later Occasions.
frameExamples: In addition, our organization will <t>work</t> on improving accountability in every department.
He pledges to  <t>conduct</t> himself  with honesty and humility.
You can list a <t><fex name='Value'>ballpark figure</fex></t> for shipping and handling.
I <t>practiced</t> my song for the play.
listRoleDefinitions: This role identifies the <fen>Act</fen> that the <fen>Agent</fen> performs intentionally.
The <fen>Agent</fen> performs the intentional act.
This role identifies the time when the Agent acts intentionally.
This role identifies the place where the intentional act occurs.
The <fen>Agent</fen> puts effort into reaching <fen>Goal</fen>.
The <fen>Goal</fen> is what the <fen>Agent</fen> expends effort to achieve.
An entity that is centrally involved in the <fen>Goal</fen> that the <fen>Agent</fen> is attempting to acheive.
This role identifies the <fen>Time</fen> when the effort occurs.
The place where the work is done.
This role marks expressions that denote the person whose conduct is being evaluated.
This role marks expressions that characterize the way that the <fen>Agent</fen> behaves.
The <fen>Time</fen> when the <fen>Agent</fen> behaves in a certain way.
The location at which the <fen>Agent</fen> exhibits their behavior.
The individual who has considered evidence or performed calculations to produce the approximation.
The position or area  on the feature scale that the <fen>Cognizer</fen> has concluded the <fen>Item</fen> occupies.
The entity that possesses a feature whose <fen>Value</fen> the <fen>Cognizer</fen> has approximated.
A proposition expressing the <fen>Cognizer</fen>'s approximation of a feature's <fen>Value</fen>.
An open proposition for which the <fen>Cognizer</fen> has approximated the <fen>Value</fen> of a variable.
The time period during which the <fen>Cognizer</fen> formed the estimate.
The location in which the <fen>Cognizer</fen> has formed their estimate.
The <fen>Entity</fen> which undergoes a change, newly ending up in the <fen>Final_category</fen> or taking on a new <fen>Final_quality</fen>.
A description of a characteristic of the <fen>Entity</fen> after the change.
The category that the <fen>Entity</fen> ends up in after the change.  Typically, this entails taking on a number of new characteristics.
>When the change occurs.
Where the change takes place.
This role identifies the <fen>Action</fen> that the <fen>Agent</fen> performs intentionally in order to prepare for a later <fen>Occasion</fen>.
The <fen>Agent</fen> performs the <fen>Action</fen> in preparation for later performances of the same type.
The later enactment or enactments that the <fen>Agent</fen> expects to perform. Note that the <fen>Agent</fen> does not have to have specific <fen>Occasion</fen>s in mind.
This role identifies the time when the <fen>Agent</fen> practices.
This role identifies the place where the practicing occurs.
